Broadbent Says QE Would Help Banking System by Stoking Growth

-- B y   S c o t t   H a m i l t o n
-- 
2011-09-26T09:17:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/broadbent-says-qe-would-help-banking-system-by-stoking-growth.html
Bank of England  policy maker Ben
Broadbent said more quantitative easing would help the banking
system.  “It would help in the sense that one of its side effects
would be to help the banking system,” Broadbent said in
response to a question about whether he thought more stimulus
would aid the economy at an event in  London  today. Still,
monetary policy shouldn’t be viewed as a cure-all, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Scott Hamilton in London at 
